'''''Valley of the Kings''''', subtitled '''''A Graphics Adventure''''', is a  video game written by Thomas M. Krischan for [[Atari 8-bit computers]] and published by Dynacomp in 1982.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Valley of the Kings |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-valley-of-the-kings_5640.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Valley of the Kings'' is a game in which the player navigates a maze of passages in ancient Egypt, obtaining valuable objects and fighting enemies.<ref name="CGW8"/>

==Reception==
David Stone reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "since {{sic|it's}} play-value is not derived from solving riddles and puzzles, but rather from maneuvering the onscreen character, there's plenty of fun to be had by replaying the adventure to try to beat your last score."<ref name="CGW8">{{cite magazine |last=Stone |first=David |title=Micro - Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Janâ€“Feb 1983 |volume=1 |issue=8 |pages=44}}</ref>

